author: dlr
msg: * subversion/libsvn_wc/status.c
(assemble_status): Remove out-dated comment about the handling of
the ENTRY parameter, and the lifetime of the pool from which it is
allocated.  These days, it's deep-copied, and allocated out of the
same pool as STATUS.

author: maxb
msg: Fix erroneous %include of apr.h into SWIG Perl and Ruby bindings, which
was causing many irrelevant APR feature macros to be imported into the core
modules. Also delete a tiny unnecessary include file, rolling its former
contents into its only site of use.
* subversion/bindings/swig/proxy/apr_h.swg: Delete file.
* subversion/bindings/swig/include/apr.swg. Integrate only the important lines
of apr_h.swg, changing the %include for an %import.

author: dlr
msg: Merge r16434, fixing the broken error reporting for "blame" in JavaHL
bindings.  Without this change, any error from svn_client_blame2() was
discarded.
Approved by:
+1: dlr
+0: djames
